    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, my blueberry bushes are starting to look kinda weird. the leaves are turning yellow but the veins are still green. i cant tell if i need more nitrogen or if the soil is just too alkaline for them. any idea what's going on?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "This symptom, called interveinal chlorosis, often suggests a nutrient uptake issue, not just a general nitrogen deficiency. Since the veins remain green while the tissue turns yellow, it strongly points toward iron or manganese deficiency, which can be exacerbated by alkaline soil pH. You should test your soil pH; if it's too high, applying amendments like elemental sulfur or chelated iron can help your bushes absorb the necessary nutrients.",
